<h2>TERMS AND CONDITIONS</h2>

<p>Londonderry Gift Card can be used only to purchase goods and services at authorized Merchants. This Card is not reloadable, not refundable, or redeemable or exchangeable for cash, and may not be used to make withdrawals or at ATMs.</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>There will be a $2.50 Account Maintenance Fee (AMF) automatically deducted each month from the Card Balance, starting 16 months after the Activation Date. If requested by you in month 15, the 16-month period will be extended to 19 months.</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>Your right to use the funds loaded onto the Card does not expire.</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<h2>PROVINCIAL GIFT CARD REGULATIONS</h2>

<p>The province of Alberta passed a gift card regulation that came into effect on November 1, 2008. The complete regulations and FAQ are available at&nbsp;<a href="http://www.servicealberta.gov.ab.ca/" rel="nofollow noreferrer" style="color: rgb(0, 136, 204); text-decoration: none; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; cursor: pointer; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgb(255, 94, 153);" target="_blank">www.servicealberta.gov.ab.ca</a>. The relevant Alberta Government FAQS are reproduced below:</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>Q: Does the regulation apply to gift cards or other kinds of prepaid purchase cards issued by financial institutions?</p>

<p>A: No. If the card is based on a direct agreement between the consumer and the financial institution that issued the card, then Alberta&#39;s gift card regulation does not apply.</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>Q: Are mall gift cards covered by the new regulations?</p>

<p>A: Yes. Mall gift cards are covered by the regulations unless the cards are issued by a financial institution and the agreement is between the card holder and the financial institution.</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>Q: What is considered to be a financial institution?</p>

<p>A: A financial institution is a bank, credit union, trust corporation or treasury branch.</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>The complete FAQs can be found on the Alberta Government website at:&nbsp;<a href="http://www.servicealberta.gov.ab.ca/" rel="nofollow noreferrer" style="color: rgb(0, 136, 204); text-decoration: none; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; cursor: pointer; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgb(255, 94, 153);" target="_blank">www.servicealberta.gov.ab.ca</a></p>

